  "prompt": "Do women lactate when they are pregnant?",
  "response": "Yes, women can begin to lactate, or produce milk, during pregnancy. This is due to hormonal changes, particularly the increase in hormones such as estrogen, progesterone, and prolactin, which prepare the breasts for milk production. Some women may notice colostrum, a thick, yellowish pre-milk fluid, leaking from their nipples during the later stages of pregnancy. However, significant milk production typically occurs after childbirth, when the hormone prolactin, stimulated by the baby's sucking, plays a major role in sustaining milk supply.",
